title.42: Adventures on the Planet of the Apes (1975) #7
title.93: Marvel Treasury Special: Captain America's Bicentennial Battles (1976) #1

description.0: Kro sets his plan of enslaving the human race to be the Deviant's foot soldiers into motion...by terrorizing the citizens of Manhattan! Will Ikaris be able to defeat this devilish plan before the humans are defeated for good?!
description.1: Ol' Greenskin is finally extracted from Glenn Talbot's mind. Will the wedding of Jarella and Hulk come to fruition?
description.2: In this issue: It's power versus power! The city is going to be crushed by the Controller if nobody stops him! Can even the Armored Avenger stand against this incredibly powerful foe?
description.3: Omega races to save a woman from jumping off of the 59th Street Bridge...but can James-Michael save himself from the bullies at school?
description.4: Thor enter's Hela's Dimension of Death to search for his father.
description.5: A trilogy of chilling Dracula tales, from a look into his past to a gruesome struggle with the undead!
description.6: Still trapped in distant space, the Fantastic Four fail in finding another planet for Galactus to consume. But as Galactus begins to destroy Counter-Earth's New York City, another hero steps up to the plate.
description.10: NOT A CHAPTER OF "PANTHER'S RAGE." This issue reprints Daredevil (1964) #69: A Panther/Daredevil team-up set in New York City!
description.18: Moon Knight must stop the deadly Conquer-Lord from carrying out an assassination on a mayoral candidate. Things take a turn for the disastrous, when Moon Knight’s lover and Girl Friday Marlene, is kidnapped and suspended over a pit of alligators! Will Moon knight be able to save both the mayor, and his girl?
description.21: The maniacal Jester seizes the public’s attention with a fake telecast starring the ‘President of the United States’. Now all costumed heroes are in trouble!
description.22: The true identity of "Katy Milner" is revealed following Ghost Rider's triumph over the mind-bending machinations of the Challenger!
description.23: The Coming of...THE CELESTIALS! Is Kro strong enough to take on the mysterious visitors within the massive space ship hovering above the City of the Space Gods?! Meanwhile, Ikaris must awaken a fellow Eternal to welcome a special guest...
description.24: Hulk is sent to an all-green world where he is reunited with his love Jarella! Is this finally Hulk's happily ever after?
description.25: Iron Man fighting side-by-side with Daredevil, the man without fear! The battle rages on-the mind boggling menace of the brooding Blood Brothers!
description.27: Mangog is revealed as the one behind the mad Odin and with possession of the Odinsword, Mangog may have already won.
description.28: Before Dracula can complete his wedding ceremony, he's interrupted - by a satanic ritual! Which of these dark schemes will prevail?
description.29: Where have all the stars gone?! It's up to Warlock to save the stars when battling the cosmic Star Thief!
description.30: The X-Men are aboard a space station with Stephen Lang, the director of an anti-mutant project known simply as Armageddon. Armageddon's goal? To wipe out all earth's mutants from the far-reaches of space! In such close quarters, tempers will surely flare.
description.31: With just 24 hours to spare, the team must split up to find another planet for Galactus to consume- sparing Counter-Earth. Will other earthly inhabitants be so keen on a new, menacing ruler?
description.38: A triple battle between Hammerhead, Dr. Octopus, and Spider-Man! But when the explosive "conflict" blows over, Peter discovers that Aunt May is in more danger than ever! Plus, Spidey's Spider-Mobile recovered at long last! And you'll never believe which villain repaired it!
description.39: The Avengers are caught in media frenzy, as they plan on revealing their next line-up of Earth's Mightiest Heroes! With Wasp and Yellowjacket fully recovered, will the two former Avengers once again join the ranks? Thor decides to leave the team to focus on Asgardian affairs, while Hawkeye decides to re-focus his efforts with the Avengers.
description.40: SPECIAL BICENTENNIAL ISSUE! On the 200th anniversary of the United Stated America will die! And only Cap can save it!
description.41: The Griffin's trying to spring Stuart Clarke from the hospital...but for what dastardly purpose? Meanwhile, Ivan and Black Widow are confronted by a ghost from Natasha's past!
description.50: Daredevil plays the upper hand against the Jester…who has falsely accused Ol’ Hornhead of murder!
description.58: Paul is an artist who is having night terrors and thankfully his neighbor Howard the Duck is here to save the day....er, night. Can Howard be his voice of reason and save his neighbor?
description.64: PANTHER'S RAGE: PART 17: Monica imagines what America's Reconstruction Era would look like had Black Panther been involved.
description.70: Spider-Man has one thing on his mind following Dr. Octopus' abduction of Aunt May. Will Spidey be reunited with his beloved aunt before Doc Ock makes his next move? Plus, a devious plot is put into action that restores Hammerhead to his corporeal body!
description.71: The Avengers and Hellcat return to their own reality. However, they soon learn that disaster will strike no matter what dimension they're in!
description.72: During a moment away from the costumed ball at his estate, William Taurey activates Big Daddy a.k.a Madbomb!
description.74: The First Appearance of the Eternals!  King Kirby's very own cosmic series starts here! Deep in the God Chamber, archeologist Daniel Damien and his daughter Margot learn from their assistant, Ike Harris (a.k.a. Ikaris the Eternal) that he must activate the Cosmic Beacon deep within the God Chamber! But Deviants Kro and Brother Tode have another plan for Ikaris in mind...
description.75: Trapped within Glenn Talbot's mind, the Hulk continues to shrink down to molecular levels! Could he possibly shrink into nonexistence? But first, a visit to Terragonia!
description.76: After a regretful farewell with Happy and Pepper, Tony returns to the very life that pushed them away in the first place. Will Tony choose to give up the Iron Man mantle? Plus: The Blood Brothers are back! And they aren't taking prisoners!
description.77: A tale of two personas! James-Michael starts his first day in public school, while Omega struggles to free himself from the clutches of Electro!
description.78: Thor fights to confort the mad Odin, but what is the true reason for the All-Father's descent into madness?
description.79: Save the date for...the WEDDING of DRACULA!? What sort of plan does Dracula have in store for this unholy marriage? Can Blade and Hannibal King stop him? And who is the mysterious man with no face?
description.80: The Fantastic Four, whisked away to Counter-Earth by the mighty Gorr! Also featuring the indomitable Galactus!
description.82: The Fantastic Four must travel back in time to WWII to fight Baron Zemo!
description.83: Daredevil and Torpedo give chase to the face-changing Chameleon!
description.88: In Manhattan, Moon Knight stages a stake-out of seven spies. Who are these mysterious masked men that have piqued the vigilante’s interest? Moon Knight teams up with trusted ally Frenchie to get to the bottom of a political plot. Featuring the many guises of the mysterious Moon Knight!
description.92: A Spider-Man vs. Deathlok team-up! Hurtling through time and space, Spider-Man finds himself in 1990, only fifteen years ahead of his own time. There, he meets a cyborg from the future who has sworn revenge against a man he calls "Ryker." After an attack from the Cubists, Spider-Man asks Deathlok to help him return to his familiar past.
description.93: Commemorating America's Bicentennial! Check out Captain America's time-bending adventure as told by Marvel legend and Cap co-creator, Jack Kirby! A history lesson through the ages...starring the First Avenger!
description.94: Under trial by the Challenger, Johnny Blaze is forced to relive the worst moments of his life. Death's Head comes a knocking for Karen Page.
description.95: The battle against the Blizzard, his most chilling super-villain of all, continues! With the climatron in his hands, the Blizzard will freeze Long Island and then the world! But not if Tony, Happy, and Pepper have something to say something about it!
description.96: The Red Skull may have taken down the Invaders, but he still must contend with the Liberty Legion.
description.97: Balder warns Thor of the madness that has overtaken Odin and upon arriving at Asgard, the God of Thunder is sentenced to die!
description.98: To stop Dracula's latest scheme, Blade must team up with Hannibal King, vampire detective!
description.99: Warlock will need all the power of the Soul Gem to take on Star Thief!

8.text: The greatest Martial Arts Master stars in his own feature! Read this Bruce Lee Special!

9.text: It's father versus son once more, as Fu Manchu reappears in Death-Day of the Golden Dagger!

10.text: Reprinting Daredevil (1964) #69: A Panther/Daredevil team-up set in New York City!

11.text: Topaz, Brother Voodoo and the Werewolf by Night are trapped in the deadly dimension of Dr. Glitternight!

14.text: At long last, Noah reveals his connection to the Mangler and the Spear. His identity now revealed, Detective Chase and Cage take to the streets to track down the Spear…but this nimble-footed agent proves a tricky capture.

15.text: Colleen Wing is played off as a pawn, forced into battle with her ally Iron Fist! Is this the end of Colleen Wing the hero? Iron Fist pulls out all the Kung Fu kicks he can, including a mystical mind-merge to reacquaint Colleen with her true memories. Master Khan makes his next move.

17.text: Henry Kissinger orders a ceasefire with Latveria, forcing the Fantastic Four back to American soil. Meanwhile, Namor senses an unusual presence; Enter Shroud, Marvel’s most mysterious mercenary! But why has Shroud agreed to take down Doom at the behest of Namor?

18.text: Moon Knight must stop the deadly Conquer-Lord from carrying out an assassination on a mayoral candidate. Things take a turn for the disastrous, when Moon Knight’s lover and Girl Friday Marlene, is kidnapped and suspended over a pit of alligators! Will Moon knight be able to save both the mayor, and his girl?

19.text: Doctor Strange and Clea time travel to 1618 London...where they meet the explorer of new worlds, Francis Bacon!

20.text: Nebulon is up to his old tricks when he transports Strange, Red Guardian, and Power Man to his dimension of terrors! Jack Norriss and Kyle Richmond align themselves to save their teammates from a fate worse than death. The return of Nighthawk.

21.text: The maniacal Jester seizes the public’s attention with a fake telecast starring the ‘President of the United States’. Now all costumed heroes are in trouble!

32.text: The White Tiger launches his own War on Crime…starting with a pack of gangsters!

33.text: Bedlam in the Great Refuge! Black Bolt goes wild!

34.text: More martial arts mayhem as Shang-Chi faces an electrifying death at the hands of Shockwave!

35.text: Tony Stark obsesses over the theft of his latest invention -- but for security reasons, he can't even tell Bill the purpose behind the device!

37.text: A hairy horror calling himself the ‘Mangler’ comes for Power Man! Noah Burstein may be concealing critical information about this assailant and the mercenary, the Spear. But why would Noah keep secrets from his closest friends?

42.text: Taylor and Nova venture deeper into the forbidden zone. Meanwhile, a new group of Astronauts crash land and are in for the surprise of their lives!

43.text: Daimon Hellstrom is attacked by the assassin known as Mindstar!

44.text: The tables turn entirely as Tigra finds herself at the wrong end of Red Wolf’s fury!

46.text: Team-up between the Thing and the Scarecrow!

47.text: Bombs away! Join in with Spider-Man and Iron Man when Captain Jean DeWolff needs help tracking down the source of a bombing in Stark International's fuel tank.

48.text: What is the celestial goliath known as the Topographical Man, and how can the Guardians of the Galaxy hope to stand against his will?

50.text: Daredevil plays the upper hand against the Jester…who has falsely accused Ol’ Hornhead of murder!

51.text: The first appearance of Rocket Raccoon. Prince Wayfinder arrives on Witch World and finds himself face-to-face with the future Guardian of the Galaxy. Note: this issue only contains the Rocket Raccoon story.

52.text: Baron Blood is out to end the Invaders as the fate of London hangs in the balance.  Thankfully, the Invaders get a little help from one of Britain's greatest heroes.

53.text: Wong enlists the help of Lord Phyffe and Rama Kaliph to free Doctor Strange and Clea from hell where they are the captors of Satan!

54.text: Doctor Strange and Red Guardian duke it out with Plantman’s giant, toxic flower. But when hallucinatory agents are added to the fray…all bets are off! Luckily Power Man is on the scene. Valkyrie struggles with her morality, and cellmates, behind bars.

56.text: Peter Parker is busy doing homework when duty calls! Spider-Man and the Thing take on Basilisk!

57.text: Continued from Marvel Two-In-One (1974) #17! Part Two of Thing and Spidey’s battle against Basilisk!

60.text: Old Skull recounts his first meeting with Killraven, as well as the earliest days of the Martian Invasion.

61.text: Deathlok is hired by the C.I.A to eliminate a threat from Hellinger. During the mission, Deathlok discovers clones of Luther Manning, and must destroy each incarnation of himself!

62.text: It’s a terrifying Tiger-centric issue, as White Tiger and the Sons of the Tiger take center stage!

63.text: Shang-Chi must defeat Shockwave in hand-to-hand combat before his time bomb detonates!

64.text: Monica imagines what America’s Reconstruction Era would look like had Black Panther been involved.

65.text: The Werewolf by Night fights Brother Voodoo!

68.text: A masked criminal named the Spear terrorizes Noah Burstein! What ‘past wrongs’ has Noah committed to deserve this attack? Luke Cage investigates.

69.text: Skull and his friends continue to experience jumps in time despite escaping the Tower. With Raymond Corey facing grave injuries, will the crew slow down for a second? There’s no rest for the wounded and weary as Skull and company thwart an attack from an Incan tribe! Outside the Bermuda Triangle, a ghost from James Scully’s past resurfaces.

73.text: Captain Marvel has gone mad! Rick Jones, usually bonded with him on world-saving missions, is now Mar-Vell's biggest target!

82.text: The Fantastic Four must travel back in time to WWII to fight Baron Zemo!

83.text: Daredevil and Torpedo give chase to the face-changing Chameleon!

85.text: Colleen Wing’s location is still classified, but Iron Fist is determined to blow the cover and rescue his friend. But before Danny can track Colleen, he must thwart an attack from angered civilians! Iron Fist makes ties to the IRA…but how? Colleen succumbs to the brainwashing powers of Angar the Screamer!

87.text: Absconded away to Latveria, Namor must remain a loyal servant to Doom, or meet his death. Will the Fantastic Four intervene in Doom’s latest attempt at world domination? You bet!

88.text: In Manhattan, Moon Knight stages a stake-out of seven spies. Who are these mysterious masked men that have piqued the vigilante’s interest? Moon Knight teams up with trusted ally Frenchie to get to the bottom of a political plot. Featuring the many guises of the mysterious Moon Knight!

89.text: A mysterious visitor craves Strange's tutelage as mystical guide. Satan emerges!

90.text: Tania Belinskaya is the Red Guardian! After performing a successful brain transplant on Norriss, Strange ensures that the Russian super woman can stay in America. Valkyrie encounters a moral dilemma in prison, while Kyle Richmond finds himself in hot water once again! What does Plantman want with Nighthawk? The Defenders can have their teammate back…to the tune of five million dollars!

91.text: A Savage Land adventure! Thing and Ka-Zar Vs. a mighty T-Rex!
